You could make use of 2 capturing groups. 

In group 1 match either `&#39;` or `&quot;` and use a [backreference](https://www.regular-expressions.info/backref.html) `\1` to match the same as what is matched in group 1 to prevent function names to start and end with a different quote like `&#39;test1&quot;`

In group 2 capture the function name.

    ([&quot;&#39;]?)([^&quot;&#39;\s{}]+)\1\s*:\s*function\(\)

In parts

- `(` Capture **group 1**
 - `[&quot;&#39;]?` Match an optional `&#39;` or `&quot;`
- `)` Close group
- `(` Capture **group 2**
 - `[^&#39;&quot;\s{}]+` Match 1+ times any char other than the listed using a [negated character class](https://www.regular-expressions.info/charclass.html#negated)
- `)\1` Close group 2
- `\s*:\s*` Match `:` between 0+ whitespace chars
- `function\(\)` Match function()

[Regex demo](https://regex101.com/r/yexJWs/1)

