Actually, question should be, Can&#39;t read props sent by parent. You are passing it correctly but reading in different context.

let&#39;s understand what does following code do?

    &lt;button onClick={this.click} ... /&gt;

This adds the click event on a button with handler associated with it. As we know, every programming language runs a code block in a specific scope/context. so for this function as we have not added any scope/context then it will be documents scope/context by default. 

To use props we need context of component SetTimer.

There are two ways,
 1. Pass the context in which you are executing the onClick.

    &lt;button onClick={this.click}

 2. Make click function as arrow function so it won&#39;t accept any context and always run in component&#39;s scope.

 

        click = () =&gt; {
           this.props.handleUpdate(this.props.value)
    
        }

